 > Cada nueva versión DEBE crear su archivo correspondiente en `changelogs/` y agregarse aquí.
 > Las entradas describen el estado del proyecto en el momento de cada release.
 
+## [v0.0.51] — 2026-06-12 — [Detalle](changelogs/v0.0.51.md)
+- Added `analyze_code` as a first-class tool for deep Python inspection, with safe path validation and loader/test coverage.
+- Updated the public docs and architecture summaries to reflect the 15-tool registry.
+- Kept the tool registry aligned with the generated `rules/` metadata.
+
+## [v0.0.50] — 2026-06-12 — [Detalle](changelogs/v0.0.50.md)
+- Fixed JS validation in `validate_javascript()` by checking a temporary file with Node instead of relying on an unsupported stdin flag.
+- Added brace-glob support to `list_files` and `search_files`, and taught `list_files` to summarize mixed-language trees without assuming Python AST payloads.
+- Added regression tests for the new validation and glob behavior.
+
+## [v0.0.49] — 2026-06-12 — [Detalle](changelogs/v0.0.49.md)
+- Removed the last session/message repository singletons from the API wrappers and background rename task.
+- Kept the same runtime behavior while moving those seams to explicit local repository creation or injection.
+- Revalidated the focused Python tests after the cleanup.
+
+## [v0.0.48] — 2026-06-12 — [Detalle](changelogs/v0.0.48.md)
+- The web stream builder now accepts an injectable `chat_stream_fn`, so the service layer no longer depends on the core chat entrypoint at import time.
+- `web/routers/chat.py` now passes the core stream function explicitly, preserving behavior while narrowing the web-to-core seam.
+- The web architecture docs were updated to describe the explicit repo injection and stream function boundary.
+
+## [v0.0.47] — 2026-06-12 — [Detalle](changelogs/v0.0.47.md)
+- Core now receives tool registry data and message repositories through explicit parameters instead of hidden module singletons.
+- History rebuild now accepts an injected message repository, and the chat route passes the shared repository explicitly.
+- The runtime keeps the same behavior, but the core seams are narrower and easier to test in isolation.
+
+## [v0.0.46] — 2026-06-12 — [Detalle](changelogs/v0.0.46.md)
+- New tools oficializadas: `search_files` y `edit_file`, con helpers compartidos para análisis y validación.
+- Hardened filesystem access: `search_files` and `edit_file` now share the same safe path policy as the other tools.
+- Docs and tests aligned: the public registry, README, and architecture summaries now reflect the real tool set.
+
 ## [v0.0.45] — 2026-06-12 — [Detalle](changelogs/v0.0.45.md)
 - Officialized the new `execute_command` tool and the improved `list_files` tool in the public docs and tests
 - Updated the tool architecture docs to reflect the 12-tool registry at that point in time
